# Module Documentation Structure

Apply this rule when creating or updating documentation for any module under `foundry-platform/`.

## Required Documents

Every module MUST have these documents:

| Document | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `README.md` | Module overview, architecture, design decisions |
| `requirements.md` | Implementation requirements: APIs, database, error handling, observability |
| `{entity}-journey.md` | End-to-end walkthrough of the module's primary flow (required if module has complex flows) |

## README.md Structure

Every module MUST have a README.md with these sections in order:

```markdown
# {Module Name}

**Module scope:** {One-line scope statement — what the module owns}

## Purpose

{2-3 paragraphs: why this module exists, what problem it solves, who benefits}

## What this module does

- **{Capability}** — {description}
{List all primary capabilities}

## What this module does NOT do

{Explicit boundaries — capabilities that belong to OTHER modules}
{Prevents scope creep and clarifies integration points}

## Architecture

{ASCII diagram or Mermaid showing:}
- Internal components
- Data flow
- Integration points with other modules

## Key Services / Components

### {Service Name}
{Brief description}
→ [{detail-doc}.md]({detail-doc}.md)

{Repeat for each major service/component}

## ACE Concepts Realized

| Concept | How this module realizes it |
|---------|----------------------------|

## Key Design Decisions

- **{Decision}** — {rationale}

## Open Questions

- {Unresolved design decisions}

## Module Documents

| Document | Content |
|----------|---------|
| [requirements.md](requirements.md) | Implementation requirements |
| [{entity}-journey.md]({entity}-journey.md) | End-to-end walkthrough |

## Read Next

- {Links to related modules and ACE conceptual docs}
```

